    parts.append('<ol>')
    parts.append('<li><strong>Before the handover:</strong> open CarShake and run the guided 8-angle scan. The app walks you through each angle so you do not miss high-risk zones like front bumper corners, rear quarter panels, and wheels. Every photo is time-stamped and geo-located automatically — no manual entry, no text overlays a user could fake.</li>')
    parts.append('<li><strong>Get the receipt scanned:</strong> CarShake generates a QR handover receipt. Have the valet, attendant, or service advisor scan it to acknowledge the vehicle condition at the moment of transfer. This single step prevents most "the damage was already there" denials.</li>')
    parts.append('<li><strong>After the handover:</strong> run the same 8-angle scan when you get the car back. CarShake compares it to the pre-handover scan and produces a side-by-side diff that highlights any new damage.</li>')
    parts.append('<li><strong>Use the diff:</strong> if new damage is present, export the before/after diff with timestamps and geo-data. This is the document you attach to the claim, dispute letter, or insurance filing.</li>')
    parts.append('</ol>')
    parts.append('<h2>What most people get wrong</h2>')
    parts.append('<ul>')
    parts.append('<li><strong>Skipping the pre-scan.</strong> The pre-scan is the entire game. Without it, the post-scan proves nothing. Sixty seconds before you hand over the keys is the highest-leverage minute in your trip.</li>')
    parts.append('<li><strong>Only photographing the obvious sides.</strong> Most valet damage happens on front and rear bumpers, corners, and wheels. The guided 8-angle scan exists to force coverage of these zones.</li>')
    parts.append('<li><strong>Not getting the receipt scanned.</strong> The QR handover receipt converts your private photo record into an acknowledged record. Operators who scan it at transfer are far less likely to dispute damage later.</li>')
    parts.append('<li><strong>Documenting damage after leaving the lot.</strong> Always run the post-scan immediately when you get the car back, while you are still on the property.</li>')
    parts.append('</ul>')
    parts.append('<h2>The economics</h2>')
    parts.append('<p>The average valet damage claim runs $2,100. A single disputed claim costs $500+ in deductibles, time, and stress. The CarShake workflow takes 60 seconds, the free tier includes 3 scans, and founding spots (73 of 100 remain) lock the $2.97/month price forever. The math is straightforward: one prevented dispute pays for roughly 14 years of CarShake.</p>')
    parts.append('</section>')
    return "\n".join(parts)


def gen_template(h1, desc, slug):
    parts = []
    parts.append('<section style="margin-top:32px">')
    parts.append('<h2>How to use this template</h2>')
    parts.append('<p>This template exists because most drivers lose damage disputes they should win — not because they are wrong, but because they do not have their evidence organized in a format the other party, their insurance, or a court can evaluate quickly. A well-structured template forces you to include the specific details that matter: the date, the location, the condition of the vehicle before and after, the identity of the operator who took custody, and the timestamped photo evidence that proves when the damage appeared.</p>')
    parts.append('<p>Use this template alongside a CarShake scan. The scan produces the time-stamped, geo-located before/after photo evidence; the template gives you the written structure to present that evidence to the operator, your insurance company, or a small claims court. Together they are the difference between a disputed claim and a resolved one.</p>')
    parts.append('<h2>What every damage documentation needs</h2>')
    parts.append('<ul>')
    parts.append('<li><strong>Date and time of handover:</strong> the exact moment you transferred custody. CarShake timestamps this automatically.</li>')
    parts.append('<li><strong>Location:</strong> the address or venue where the handover occurred. CarShake geo-locates every scan.</li>')
    parts.append('<li><strong>Pre-handover condition:</strong> a guided 8-angle photo set of the vehicle before you handed over the keys.</li>')
    parts.append('<li><strong>Post-handover condition:</strong> the same 8-angle photo set taken immediately when you got the car back.</li>')
    parts.append('<li><strong>The diff:</strong> a side-by-side comparison that isolates any new damage that appeared during the handover window.</li>')
    parts.append('<li><strong>Operator acknowledgement:</strong> the QR handover receipt the valet, attendant, or advisor scanned at the moment of transfer.</li>')
    parts.append('</ul>')
    parts.append('<h2>Why templates alone are not enough</h2>')
    parts.append('<p>A template gives you structure. It does not give you evidence. The evidence — the time-stamped, geo-located, acknowledged photos — has to come from a tool like CarShake that bakes metadata into the capture process. Drivers who try to build this evidence manually with a phone camera almost always lose, because there is no way to prove when and where a standalone photo was taken. CarShake solves this by capturing everything in a single guided workflow that takes 60 seconds.</p>')
    parts.append('<h2>The economics</h2>')
    parts.append('<p>The average valet damage claim runs $2,100. A single disputed claim costs $500+ in deductibles, time, and stress. Pair this template with a CarShake scan on your next handover and the entire documentation package takes 60 seconds. The free tier includes 3 scans — enough to prove the workflow fits your life before paying anything. Founding spots (73 of 100 remain) lock the $2.97/month price forever.</p>')
    parts.append('</section>')
    return "\n".join(parts)


