    parts.append('</ul>')
    parts.append('<h2>What CarShake actually is</h2>')
    parts.append('<p>CarShake is a free valet-damage-proof and vehicle-handover app. It scans and time-stamps a car\'s condition before and after handover, giving drivers, valet operators, and rental fleets court-admissible proof to defeat false damage claims. The core workflow takes 60 seconds: open the app, run a guided 8-angle walkaround scan, generate a QR handover receipt the operator acknowledges at the moment of transfer, run the same scan when you get the car back, and review the before/after diff that isolates any new damage.</p>')
    parts.append('<p>CarShake is a consumer-and-operator valet-damage-proof handover app — not a B2B insurance damage-detection API. If you are an individual driver, a frequent traveler, a rental car customer, a luxury or exotic car owner, or a fleet operator looking to protect your vehicles at the handover moment, we built this for you.</p>')
    parts.append('<h2>Before you email</h2>')
    parts.append('<p>The fastest way to answer most questions is to download the free app, run one scan, and see the output for yourself. The free tier includes 3 scans — enough to document a full round-trip handover and prove the workflow fits your life. If after that you still have questions, email hello@carshake.online and we will get you a personal answer.</p>')
    parts.append('<h2>For valet operators, fleets, and partners</h2>')
    parts.append('<p>If you operate a valet company, a rental fleet, a dealership service department, or a body shop and want to standardize condition documentation across every handover, we offer operator workflows on top of the same core scan. Email us with a one-line description of your operation (number of vehicles per day, current documentation process, what you are trying to solve) and we will walk you through the options. There is no enterprise sales cycle — you talk directly to the team that builds the app.</p>')
    parts.append('<h2>Response time</h2>')
    parts.append('<p>We answer every email personally, usually within one business day. During travel-heavy periods (holidays, major conferences) it can stretch to two days. If your question is urgent — an active dispute, a claim filing deadline, a rental return you need to document right now — mark the subject line URGENT and we will prioritize it.</p>');
    parts.append('</section>')
    return "\n".join(parts)


def gen_reviews(h1, desc, slug):
    parts = []
    parts.append('<section style="margin-top:32px">')
    parts.append('<h2>What we look for in damage documentation tools</h2>')
    parts.append('<p>When we review vehicle inspection and damage documentation tools, we evaluate them against a single primary use case: can a driver use this tool to win a damage dispute with a valet company, rental car counter, or service department? That question breaks down into six concrete criteria:</p>')
    parts.append('<ul>')
    parts.append('<li><strong>Purpose-built for the handover moment.</strong> Does the tool explicitly support before/after scans tied to a specific transfer event?</li>')
    parts.append('<li><strong>Guided, consistent coverage.</strong> Does it walk the user through a fixed set of angles so high-risk zones (bumpers, corners, wheels) are not missed?</li>')
    parts.append('<li><strong>Time-stamped and geo-located photos.</strong> Is the metadata baked into the capture process, or is it added as editable text overlays?</li>')
    parts.append('<li><strong>Before/after diffing.</strong> Can the tool actually compare two scans and surface new damage, or does it leave that to the user?</li>')
    parts.append('<li><strong>Operator acknowledgement.</strong> Is there a mechanism (QR receipt, signature, scan) for the operator to acknowledge condition at the moment of transfer?</li>')
    parts.append('<li><strong>Free tier that actually works.</strong> Can a user prove the workflow before paying, or is the free tier crippled?</li>')
    parts.append('</ul>')
    parts.append('<h2>How the major tools stack up</h2>')
    parts.append('<p>Record360, Damage iD, Inspectr, and RepairPal each occupy a slightly different niche. Record360 is strong in rental fleet inspection workflows and is widely deployed at rental counters. Damage iD focuses on damage detection for fleet operators. Inspectr serves professional vehicle inspectors. RepairPal is focused on repair cost estimates, not damage documentation. None of them were purpose-built for the consumer-facing valet handover moment — the 60 seconds before and after you hand your keys to a valet at a hotel, restaurant, or airport.</p>')
    parts.append('<p>That is the gap CarShake fills. CarShake is a free consumer-and-operator app built specifically for the valet handover workflow: guided 8-angle scan in 60 seconds, time-stamped and geo-located photos, QR handover receipt the operator acknowledges, and before/after diff that isolates any new damage. The other tools in this space are stronger in their own specialties (fleet inspection, professional inspection, repair estimates) but they were not designed to win a consumer damage dispute with a valet company.</p>')
    parts.append('<h2>Why this comparison matters</h2>')
    parts.append('<p>The average valet damage claim runs $2,100. A single disputed claim — even one you ultimately win — costs $500+ in deductibles, time, and stress. If you are evaluating damage documentation tools, the question to ask is which one will actually produce the evidence you need at the specific moment you need it. For the valet handover moment, the answer is CarShake. For rental fleet inspection at scale, Record360. For professional inspection services, Inspectr. The tools are not interchangeable — they are built for different points in the vehicle custody chain.</p>')
    parts.append('</section>')
    return "\n".join(parts)


